</taxonomicName>
and its synonym 
<taxonomicName id="CBE598E2FFA7FFBB17A6FABAB5BEFA80" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1908" box="[746,905,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conspicuus">
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA7FFBB17A6FABAB4C9FA80" box="[746,766,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="237">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA7FFBB1641FABAB5BEFA80" box="[781,905,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="237">conspicuus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were described from an unspecified number of specimens (
<typeStatus id="D35E5DC3FFA7FFBB1456FADEB74FFAAD" box="[282,376,1375,1401]" pageId="12" pageNumber="237">syntype</typeStatus>
(s)), the former with the following data: “ 
<collectingCountry id="74F2A3F1FFA7FFBB1676FADEB5A6FAAD" box="[826,913,1375,1401]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="12" pageNumber="237">Ceylon</collectingCountry>
. Coll. Dohrn”, and the latter with the following data: “ 
<collectingCountry id="74F2A3F1FFA7FFBB15ACFA02B700FA49" box="[224,311,1411,1437]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="12" pageNumber="237">Ceylon</collectingCountry>
; Peradeniya (Green)”. A variety of 
<taxonomicName id="CBE598E2FFA7FFBB1781FA02B559FA48" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1908" box="[717,878,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conspicuus">
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA7FFBB1781FA02B4D6FA48" box="[717,737,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="237">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA7FFBB17BEFA02B559FA48" box="[754,878,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="237">conspicuus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with part of the face testaceous, was figured by Distant. 
<bibRefCitation id="68749E90FFA7FFBB15BBFA26B7C0FA16" author="Zhang, Y. L. &amp; Webb, M. D." box="[247,503,1447,1474]" pageId="12" pageNumber="237" pagination="1 - 103" refId="ref11914" refString="Zhang, Y. L. &amp; Webb, M. D. (1996) A revised classification of the Asian and Pacific Selenocephalinae leafhoppers (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Bulletin of the Natural History Museum, Entomology Series, 65, 1 - 103." type="journal article" year="1996">Zhang &amp; Webb (1996)</bibRefCitation>
designated a male as the 
<typeStatus id="D35E5DC3FFA7FFBB1657FA26B5B5FA15" box="[795,898,1447,1473]" pageId="12" pageNumber="237">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="CBE598E2FFA7FFBB16E5FA26B27AFA15" baseAuthorityName="Stal" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[937,1101,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbaticeps">
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA7FFBB16E5FA26B58AFA14" box="[937,957,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="237">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA7FFBB1680FA26B27AFA15" box="[972,1101,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="237">limbaticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and synonymised the species with 
<taxonomicName id="CBE598E2FFA7FFBB159CFA4AB759FA30" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1908" box="[208,366,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conspicuus">
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA7FFBB159CFA4AB6D3FA30" box="[208,228,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="237">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA7FFBB15BEFA4AB759FA30" box="[242,366,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="237">conspicuus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but treated the latter junior name as the valid name in error. 
<bibRefCitation id="68749E90FFA7FFBB115EFA4AB2F6FA31" author="Lu, L. &amp; Webb, M. D. &amp; Zhang, Y." box="[1042,1217,1483,1509]" pageId="12" pageNumber="237" pagination="237 - 246" refId="ref11288" refString="Lu, L., Webb, M. D. &amp; Zhang, Y. (2019) A new species of the leafhopper genus Drabescus Stal (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae: Deltocephalinae) from China, with a checklist and key to species. Zootaxa, 4612 (2), 237 - 246. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4612.2.6" type="journal article" year="2019">
Lu 
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA7FFBB1174FA4AB25EFA31" box="[1080,1129,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="237">et al</emphasis>
. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
corrected this error in their checklist. 
<taxonomicName id="CBE598E2FFA7FFBB142AFA6EB43CF9DD" baseAuthorityName="Stal" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[358,523,1519,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbaticeps">
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA7FFBB142AFA6EB43CF9DD" box="[358,523,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="237">D. limbaticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has very distinctive pronotal colour pattern (see Remarks under the genus) and relatively short sub-basal processes of the aedeagus compared to other species of 
<taxonomicName id="CBE598E2FFA7FFBB1170F992B283F9F9" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1870" box="[1084,1204,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA7FFBB1170F992B283F9F9" box="[1084,1204,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="237">Drabescus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the subcontinent. The habitus image of 
<taxonomicName id="CBE598E2FFA7FFBB14C1F9B6B41BF984" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1908" box="[397,556,1591,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conspicuus">
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA7FFBB14C1F9B6B41BF984" box="[397,556,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="237">D. conspicuus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(fig. 530) figured by 
<bibRefCitation id="68749E90FFA7FFBB166DF9B6B217F986" author="Zhang, Y. L. &amp; Webb, M. D." box="[801,1056,1591,1618]" pageId="12" pageNumber="237" pagination="1 - 103" refId="ref11914" refString="Zhang, Y. L. &amp; Webb, M. D. (1996) A revised classification of the Asian and Pacific Selenocephalinae leafhoppers (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Bulletin of the Natural History Museum, Entomology Series, 65, 1 - 103." type="journal article" year="1996">Zhang &amp; Webb (1996)</bibRefCitation>
is a 
<typeStatus id="D35E5DC3FFA7FFBB1119F9B6B2DBF985" box="[1109,1260,1591,1617]" pageId="12" pageNumber="237">paralectotype</typeStatus>
and not a 
<typeStatus id="D35E5DC3FFA7FFBB102FF9B6B6F0F9A1" pageId="12" pageNumber="237">paratype</typeStatus>
as mentioned by them.
</paragraph>
